//Congential heart disease - Transposition of the great arteries (TGA)


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 of Cardio MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
When I select 'Congential heart disease' tab
Then 'Congential heart disease' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Transposition of the great arteries (TGA)' from 'Congential heart disease' dropdown menu
Then 'Add pathology' button is enabled
And 'Levo-Transposition (L-TGA)' radio button is enabled
And 'Dextro-Transposition (D-TGA)' radio button is enabled

And 'Ventricle septal defect (VSD)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Atrial septal defect (ASD)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Persistent ductus arteriosus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Persistent foramen ovale' checkbox is enabled
